Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tariq T Sullivan Jackson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Arial Jade Rosenberg in court for Tariq T Sullivan Jackson.  Attorney Patrick J Anderson in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defendant's appearance is waived. Defense withdraws the speedy trial demand. Defense requested motion hearing date.  State's response, if appropriate, to be filed on or before 11/18/2022.  Defendant to appear by zoom on the next court date. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Motion hearing scheduled for November 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
State's Motion to Review Dismissal By Judicial Court Commissioner.  Received and Filed.  nk
Defendant enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND. Exp 12/29/2022

10:30 AM Defendant Tariq T Sullivan Jackson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Arial Jade Rosenberg appeared by video for Tariq T Sullivan Jackson.  Prosecuting attorney Thomas Hasle in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer W. Del Moral. During testimony the defendant voluntarily left the booth. Court will adjourn the matter. The defendant returned to the booth. Preliminary hearing continues. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial. On it's own motion the Court dismissed the enhancer of habitual criminality repeater. Information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 11.
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Case is set for a Preliminary Hearing. Defendant is unable to appear by video from Columbia County due email issues. State's Witness is not present but a subpoena was sent out. Defense motions to dismiss. Court acknowledges the motion. Case is adjourned. Court orders case adjourned for CAUSE for  a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.
